OL,3,CHow the cost of living is impacting
OL,4,Cblind and partially sighted people
OL,6,FMs Williams continued: "Blind and
OL,7,Fpartially sighted people are much more
OL,8,Flikely to live in lower income
OL,9,Fhouseholds and they face significant
OL,10,Fadditional spends, things they can't
OL,11,Favoid spending on like taxis,
OL,12,Fequipment, technology.
OL,14,F"We spoke to 110 blind and partially
OL,15,Fsighted people. One quarter of them
OL,16,Ftold us that they spend over #100 per
OL,17,Fmonth on these additional, unavoidable
OL,18,Fcosts and one fifth told us that they
OL,19,Fspend over #200 on these additional,
OL,20,Funavoidable costs.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G12/16
